 SCRATCH MONKEY (skrach muhn'kee) n. As in, "Before testing or reconfiguring,
always mount a". Used in memory of Mabel, the Swimming Wonder Monkey who
expired when a computer vendor PM'd a machine which was regulating the gas
mixture that the monkey was breathing at the time. see Appendix A. A mantram
used to advise caution when dealing with irreplacable data or devices. see
SCRATCH.